	The consensus was that the best way to isolate a domain is to make
those name servers think they are root servers and don't tell them about
any of the real root servers.  This can be done in the cache file.

	Thanks to all who sent me helpful suggestions.  This list has
taught me a lot about DNS.  This was just the latest nut to crack.  :-)

	--Kent

